`SubscriptionObserver_set_ref` (`subscription_observer.cpp:160-166`) is declared as returning `PyObject*` but is registered as a setter in `PyGetSetDef` (which requires `int` return: 0 success, -1 error).

**Current code**:
```cpp
PyObject*
SubscriptionObserver_set_ref( SubscriptionObserver* self, PyObject* value, void* context )
{
    if( value != Py_None )
    {
        return cppy::type_error("ref can only be set to None");
    }
    cppy::replace( &self->ref, Py_None );
    return 0;
}
```

**Problems**:
- Success path returns `0` (as `PyObject*` = NULL), which when cast to `int` is 0 (correct by accident)
- Error path returns `cppy::type_error(...)` which returns NULL (`PyObject*` 0) after setting the exception — also cast to `int` 0, meaning the error path **appears to succeed**. The TypeError is set but the caller sees success and does not check for it. The error is silently swallowed.

**Fix**:
```cpp
int
SubscriptionObserver_set_ref( SubscriptionObserver* self, PyObject* value, void* context )
{
    if( value != Py_None )
    {
        cppy::type_error("ref can only be set to None");
        return -1;
    }
    cppy::replace( &self->ref, Py_None );
    return 0;
}
```

Found by [cext-review-toolkit](https://github.com/devdanzin/cext-review-toolkit).
